                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MESSRS. BODKIN</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">and</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">STURGEON</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">conducted the Prosecution</hi>.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350615-name-1214" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-1214" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-1214" type="surname" value="SIMPSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-1214" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN SIMPSON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a chandler, and live in St. Alban's-street, Lam<lb></lb>beth. The prisoner came to my shop about half-past nine o'clock at night, on the 6th of June, and asked for half an ounce of tobacco—I weighed the tobacco—he gave me a counterfeit shilling—I told him it was a bad one—he said he had taken it by selling things in the street—I told him I much doubted it, and gave him in charge—I marked the shilling in the presence of the officer, and gave it into his hands.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350615-name-1215" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-1215" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-1215" type="surname" value="METHERILL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-1215" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>JOSEPH METHERILL</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">policeman L</hi> 142.) On the night of the 6th of June I was on duty near Mr. Simpson's shop—he called me and gave the prisoner in charge—he said he had given him a bad shilling—I searched him, and found another bad shilling on him and some duplicates.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350615-name-1216" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-1216" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-1216" type="surname" value="FIELD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-1216" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN FIELD</persName>
                  </hi>. I am an inspector of counterfeit coin to the Mint. These are both counterfeit, and impressions from the same mould.</p>
